HEADWORD: Cantor
<hw>Can"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., a singer, fr.
<ets>caner</ets> to sing.]</ety> <def>A singer; esp. the leader of a
church choir; a precentor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>cantor</qex> of the church intones the Te Deum.</q>
<rj><qau>Milman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cantoral</ent>⟦br⟧
